On Wed, 16 Jun 1999, Ingo Molnar wrote:
>why are you assuming that just because a task wakes another task up it
>goes to sleep immediately?? In a large amount of cases thats not true.
>(bw_tcp is just one example) 
If the current-rescheduled task doesn't go to sleep immediatly then the
wakenup task will be the one that will have to wait in the _run_queue.
